entity.description: Action from the oldest tennis tournament in the world and widely regarded as the most prestigious.

entity.name: Day 2
entity.description: All the action from the second day of The Championships at Wimbledon. The defending champion in the women's singles usually opens play on Centre Court, but Ash Barty's shock retirement means that honour will fall to another player in 2022. Former junior champion Iga Swiatek has been in dominant form in Barty's absence, but there are plenty of other contenders in the mix in what promises to be a fascinating women's singles tournament. Coverage by Sue Barker and Isa Guha.

entity.name: Day 2
entity.description: Sue Barker presents live coverage from the All England Club, as day three of Wimbledon 2022 continues. Britain's challenge this year will come from the likes of Andy Murray, Cameron Norrie and Dan Evans, along with teenager Emma Raducanu, whose fairytale win at the US Open last year catapulted her onto the world stage.
